# MERN Chat Application

## 📌 Overview
The **MERN Chat Application** is a real-time messaging platform built using the **MERN stack** (MongoDB, Express.js, React, and Node.js). It supports **one-on-one and group chat**, user authentication, and multimedia sharing.

## 🚀 Features
- **User Authentication** (Sign Up, Login, JWT-based Authentication)
- **Real-time Messaging** using Socket.io
- **One-on-One & Group Chat Support**
- **Media Uploads** (Images, Files using Cloudinary)
- **Online/Offline Status Indication**
- **Responsive UI** built with React and TailwindCSS
- **MongoDB Atlas for Database**

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
### **Frontend:**
- React.js
- Tailwind CSS
- Zustand for state management
- Axios for API requests

### **Backend:**
- Node.js
- Express.js
- MongoDB Atlas
- Socket.io for real-time communication
- Cloudinary for media storage
- JWT Authentication

## 📂 Folder Structure
```
fullstack-chat-app/
├── backend/
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── controllers/     # API controllers
│   │   ├── models/          # MongoDB models
│   │   ├── routes/          # Express routes
│   │   ├── middleware/      # Authentication & other middlewares
│   │   ├── lib/             # Utility functions & services (e.g., Socket, Cloudinary)
│   │   ├── server.js        # Main server file
│   ├── package.json
│   ├── .env.example        # Environment variables (rename to .env)
│
├── frontend/
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── components/      # React components
│   │   ├── pages/           # Application pages
│   │   ├── store/           # Zustand store for state management
│   │   ├── App.jsx          # Main React App component
│   ├── package.json
│
├── README.md
├── .gitignore
```

## 🔧 Setup Instructions
### **1. Clone the Repository**
```sh
git clone https://github.com/bhargavreddi7889/Mern-Chat_application.git
cd Mern-Chat_application
```

### **2. Backend Setup**
```sh
cd backend
npm install  # Install dependencies
cp .env.example .env  # Create .env file and configure it
node src/server.js  # Start the server
```

### **3. Frontend Setup**
```sh
cd ../frontend
npm install  # Install dependencies
npm run dev  # Start the frontend
```

### **4. Running the Application**
- Open **http://localhost:3000/** in your browser to access the chat application.
- Backend runs on **http://localhost:5000/** by default.

## ⚡ API Endpoints
| Endpoint             | Method | Description             |
|---------------------|--------|-------------------------|
| `/api/auth/register` | POST   | User Registration       |
| `/api/auth/login`    | POST   | User Login             |
| `/api/users`        | GET    | Get all users          |
| `/api/messages`     | POST   | Send message           |
| `/api/groups`       | POST   | Create Group Chat      |

